@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Aquarium Adventures";
}

<div class="container text-center">

    <h1 class="fw-bold text-primary mt-4">Welcome to Kenzie's Aquarium Adventures</h1>
    <!-- Top Centered Image -->
    <div class="mt-4">
        <img src="~/images/famaqua.JPG" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-lg" alt="Aquarium Entrance" style="max-width: 70%;">
    </div>
    <!-- Hobby Description -->
    <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm text-start">
        <p class="fs-5">
            Ever since I was young, I have been fascinated by the ocean and the incredible diversity of marine life.
            Visiting aquariums has become one of my favorite hobbies because it allows me to experience the beauty of
            the underwater world up close. Whether it's watching jellyfish float gracefully or observing the powerful
            movements of sharks, every trip to the aquarium is an adventure.
        </p>

        <p class="fs-5">
            One of the things I love most about aquariums is the sense of peace they bring. The calming blue tones,
            the slow movements of the fish, and the gentle sound of water create a relaxing atmosphere. Aquariums also
            serve as an important tool for marine conservation, educating people about the importance of protecting
            ocean ecosystems and preserving endangered species.
        </p>

        <p class="fs-5">
            Some of my favorite aquariums to visit are the <strong>Georgia Aquarium</strong>, <strong>Monterey Bay Aquarium</strong>, and
            <strong>Shedd Aquarium</strong>. Each one offers breathtaking exhibits, from giant whale sharks to mesmerizing coral
            reefs. Exploring these aquariums has deepened my appreciation for marine life, and I hope to continue
            visiting new ones in the future.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Aquarium Images Moved Below Paragraphs -->
    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="~/images/aquarium1.png" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" alt="Aquarium Scene">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="~/images/aquarium2.png" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" alt="Colorful Fish">
        </div>
    </div>

    <a href="@Url.Action("Calculator", "Home")" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg mt-4 shadow">Check My Tutoring Rates</a>
</div>


